{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/mms-last-attempt","sessionId":"adb72d37-dfad-4621-b289-1547f6c9a61d","version":"2.0.76","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a48763f","slug":"swirling-purring-ripple","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"# TASK: Explore ~/antonio/mms to understand what exists\n\nThe user has MONTHS of work in ~/antonio/mms that needs to be understood properly.\n\n## OBJECTIVES\n1. Find the RFQ (Request for Quotation) document - what did the client actually ask for?\n2. Find mockups, designs, wireframes - what should the system LOOK like?\n3. Find product requirements - what features are needed?\n4. Find the DESIGN_SPEC or similar documents\n5. Understand the folder structure - what attempts exist?\n\n## SEARCHES TO PERFORM\n1. ls -la ~/antonio/mms/ - see top level structure\n2. Find any RFQ files: find ~/antonio/mms -name \"*rfq*\" -o -name \"*RFQ*\" -o -name \"*request*\"\n3. Find any design/mockup files: find ~/antonio/mms -type f \\( -name \"*.png\" -o -name \"*.jpg\" -o -name \"*.pdf\" -o -name \"*mockup*\" -o -name \"*design*\" -o -name \"*spec*\" \\)\n4. Find markdown specs: find ~/antonio/mms -name \"*.md\" | head -50\n5. Look for DESIGN_SPEC.md or similar\n\n## OUTPUT\nReturn a comprehensive list of:\n- Key documents found (RFQ, specs, designs)\n- Folder structure\n- What each major folder contains\n- Paths to the most important files that define WHAT should be built"},"uuid":"d8fd1964-e128-4d7a-8e1c-a0c58e6ea3cc","timestamp":"2026-01-06T18:31:53.976Z"}
